      "text": [
        "هَا لَحْمُ جَزُورٍ وَقَعَ فِيهَا أُوقِيَّةٌ مِنْ دَمٍ أَ يُؤْكَلُ مِنْهَا قَالَ \"نَعَمْ فَإِنَّ اَلنَّارَ تَأْكُلُ اَلدَّمَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4211 - Sa'eed Al-A'raj asked Abu Abdullah (as), about a pot containing camel meat into which an ounce of blood had fallen.\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, it can be eaten because the fire consumes the blood.\""
        ]
      }
